body.name: ANRABESS Womens Square Neck Sleeveless Bodice Dress Side Slit Flare Mini Dresses
features: Comfortable Material: Made of lightweight, breathable, and buttery-soft stretch fabric, our dress is designed to fit comfortably and move with you. The thick, double-lined fabric is not see-through and falls at an above-the-knee length.

Flattering Design: This dress features a tight-cut bodice, square neckline, tapered shoulder straps, and a high waist that flares out into a basic mini dress. Whether you're looking for a summer dress, elegant formal wear, or simply a stretchy sexy dress, this is the dress for you!

Versatile Match: This square-neck bodycon dress can be worn with a sleeveless tank top and pairs well with jackets or leggings for colder days. Whether it's spring, summer, fall, or winter, this dress is perfect for any occasion.

Occasion-Friendly: This dress is perfect for any occasion, from street shots and vacations to parties and clubs. It's perfect for a night out, casual events, and daily life. It's also a great active tennis dresses. Perfect gift for women, ladies, and teen girls alike.

Easy Care: Our dress is easy to clean – Recommend hand wash or delicate cycle with cold water and no bleach. Available in sizes S (31" bust), M (33" bust), L (36" bust) and XL (39" bust) this dress is flat measured and comes with great stretch.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars ANRABESS Womens Square Neck Mini Dress Sleeveless Slim Fit Double Lined Short Active Tennis
reviews.reviewText: I recently added the ANRABESS Women's Square Neck Mini Dress to my collection, and it's another win from a brand I trust. As a fan of Anrabess, I appreciate the stylish design and quality of their pieces. The only downside is that it doesn't come with shorts underneath, which would have been a great addition. Nevertheless, I'm excited to wear this dress during the summer – it's a chic choice for any warm-weather occasion.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sleeveless Sunshine: A Mini That Almost Made the Full Cut
reviews.reviewText: Finding the right summer dress can feel like a treasure hunt, but this one is a pretty decent find. When it comes to style meets comfort, this number had me at 'summer sleeveless'. The fabric is soft and welcoming, almost like a gentle hug on a hot day. And with its double lining, I commend the discreet nod to quality and modesty it provides.But alas, not all is perfect. The neckline, oh so squarely cut, presents a bit of a conundrum. As much as I love the uniqueness it tries to bring, it dips too low, making it a game of hide and seek with a normal bra. Thankfully, my strapless bra stepped up to the challenge, becoming the unlikely hero of my wardrobe once more.What I appreciate, though, is the slim fit design that contours gracefully, complementing the active, on-the-go lifestyle that my family and I embody. Be it a quick roundabout with the kids in the garden or a spontaneous trip to the local market, this dress seems to keep up.And so, it hangs proudly in my closet, a testament to versatility with a hint of rebellion against conventional necklines. Whether it's for a breezy day out or a light workout session (certainly not one including somersaults unless pairing with shorts), this dress is game - just be sure to have a strapless bra on standby.

reviews.reviewText: Bought this in the hunter green color and was very impressed w the quality so bought a second one in black and both black dresses were not a good quality. The green was buttery soft and the black felt work and pilly

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I've rolled dice on a number of tennis dresses trying to find that perfect fit. Sometimes they are tight (preferable) with two layers, one to compress my body, and the other to conceal that hot mess in the first layer. Sometimes they're thin, and reveal everything.I was very surprised with this dress. It is tight and has two layers, and my silhouette looks great in it. It's got a slight A-line to it which goes on to conceal my hip dents without being bodycon all the way down.I don't like that there is no attached short, no detachable short, no anything to close it up from the bottom. This is a mini dress, so be sure to wear underwear or modesty shorts if you're planning to run around and fall on your face or back. I also am not super jazzed about the appearance of the square neck. It's just not as flattering as maybe a V would have been, but this I can't hold against the maker as it's clear this is what it was when I ordered. It just doesn't look as great in person.It's a really flattering mini dress that I might just wear for aesthetics more than athletics.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The sizing is off it runs big so beware to check the size chart. Beautiful color and nice material to workout in or do sports. I love the built in bottom but def size down.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love the double layer
reviews.reviewText: Very flattering dress. I am 5'8 and usually a size 14, hourglass-shaped and I feel that I could've gotten away with a size smaller. The waist flairs out if you are sensitive to your lower belly. The material is comfortable and I feel that the square neck is more flattering on a larger bust than a v-neck which can feel a bit too much. It is double layered which is nice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Can be worn any time!
reviews.reviewText: I pair this with a denim jacket and get compliments on it wherever I go. Remove the jacket and it is a workout dress. I would not wear this to the gym because it does not have built-in shorts but I do wear it at home for using my virtual reality headset.To me, I just prefer it as the cutest summer dress and it has great support to it is very flattering as well.So comfortable that I wear it all day when I have lots to do around the house.Fits as expected, very flattering, great color, washes well, stain resistant.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not what I was hoping for
reviews.reviewText: I was hoping that this dress would fit more accurately to how it is pictured, but it is just not flattering on my body whatsoever. There is just too much fabric it seems like; it is just gaping open in several places.I will say the material is buttery-soft and smooth which is great, but the sizing is overall off if you ask me.I wanted to love this but it was not for me.
